Reasoning: 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes joint user activity identification and channel estimation schemes, and analyzes the packet delay and throughput of the proposed schemes. This falls under the scope of information theory.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper focuses on improving the efficiency of random access schemes for machine-type communications (MTC), which is a networking and internet architecture topic.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a decentralized transmission control scheme, which falls under the scope of systems and control.
- cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper proposes an efficient data decoding algorithm for the coded slotted ALOHA (CSA) scheme, which can be applied to multimedia communications.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): Although not the main focus of the paper, the proposed schemes may have implications for security and cryptography in MTC.
